The following uses are prohibited in a home occupation:
Appliance and small engine repair;
Auto repair, major and minor;
Auto painting;
Carpentry/cabinet making;
Dance studios;
Furniture construction;
Machine shops;
Rental businesses;
Tow truck services;
Welding shops;
Other uses not listed as a permitted use.
Section 10.2 Accessory Uses and Structures.
A.
Swimming pools are considered an accessory structure.
B.
The following structures are not permitted as an accessory structure in any district.
1)
Manufactured homes
2)
Tractor trailer containers, tractor trailer beds or similar structures that were originally
designed for the transportation of goods.
